WEBVTT

03:07.647 --> 03:09.649
[Bird calling]

03:09.858 --> 03:11.860
[Singing]

03:12.068 --> 03:14.445
<i>Where do I begin?
I don't know.</i>

03:14.654 --> 03:16.447
<i>I guess with the idea</i>

03:16.656 --> 03:19.742
<i>that sometimes things happen
that we don't understand.</i>

03:19.951 --> 03:23.746
<i>Maybe we shouldn't try
to understand those things.</i>

03:23.955 --> 03:25.748
<i>My dad was assigned
to inspect</i>

03:25.957 --> 03:28.501
<i>the military Southern sector
of the E.P.A.</i>

03:28.710 --> 03:30.545
<i>My stepmother,
half brother, and I</i>

03:30.753 --> 03:33.089
<i>had to spend two months
on the road with him.</i>

03:33.298 --> 03:36.176
<i>I can tell you it's not easy
being stuck in a car</i>

03:36.384 --> 03:40.263
<i>with a 6-year-old and the woman
who replaced your mom.</i>

03:40.471 --> 03:44.559
<i>Then again nobody asked me
what I wanted to do.</i>

03:44.767 --> 03:47.520
<i>I guess things do happen
for a reason...</i>

03:47.729 --> 03:50.690
<i>Even if you don't like
what that reason is.</i>

04:17.425 --> 04:18.718
Come on.

04:18.927 --> 04:20.845
My bottom
is so sore.

04:23.514 --> 04:25.558
Fill it up,
will you?

04:25.767 --> 04:27.018
You got a rest room?

04:27.227 --> 04:29.854
Yes. It ain't great,
but we got one.

04:30.063 --> 04:31.272
Which part?

04:31.481 --> 04:32.815
Mom, can I have a soda?

04:33.024 --> 04:33.942
Hi.

04:34.150 --> 04:35.735
I see you're
from Washington, D.C.

04:35.944 --> 04:37.028
Long way from home.

04:37.237 --> 04:38.571
We sure are.

04:58.675 --> 05:02.095
You're fast.
You're fast. You're fast.

05:03.263 --> 05:05.515
You're scared. Good.

05:08.685 --> 05:10.853
They're out there.

05:11.062 --> 05:12.397
They're everywhere.

05:12.605 --> 05:14.983
They get you
when you sleep.

05:15.191 --> 05:17.068
They get you
when you sleep,
you hear?

05:17.277 --> 05:19.946
Get out. Get out,
or you'll be next.

05:21.781 --> 05:24.409
Dad! Dad!

05:24.617 --> 05:26.411
Dad, there's
a psycho in there!

05:26.619 --> 05:27.453
In the bathroom?

05:27.662 --> 05:29.497
He's got a knife.

05:31.291 --> 05:32.458
Sweetheart?

05:32.667 --> 05:34.502
Maybe you should
let him go in first.

05:34.711 --> 05:36.379
He's got the gun.

05:36.587 --> 05:38.923
Marti, maybe
you'd better come
back here, honey.

05:39.757 --> 05:40.925
Marti?

05:45.096 --> 05:46.681
There's
nothing here.

05:46.889 --> 05:49.559
There's no one
in there, honey.

05:51.436 --> 05:52.395
You okay?

05:52.603 --> 05:53.938
There's
no one there?

05:55.356 --> 05:57.233
Marti,
are you okay?

05:58.359 --> 06:00.194
Honey, are you
alright?

06:00.361 --> 06:02.196
What did
he look like?

06:02.405 --> 06:04.615
Maybe we should
call the police.

06:04.824 --> 06:07.035
<i>"They get you
when you sleep."</i>

06:07.243 --> 06:09.454
<i>I remember thinking
he was crazy,</i>

06:09.662 --> 06:11.456
<i>but I also remember thinking</i>

06:11.664 --> 06:14.751
<i>we spend half
our lives asleep.</i>

06:19.255 --> 06:20.590
Morning, sir.

06:20.798 --> 06:23.217
Hi. I'm Steve Malone.
I'm with the E.P.A.

06:23.426 --> 06:25.845
General Platt's
expecting us.

06:26.054 --> 06:27.347
One moment, please.

06:36.814 --> 06:39.692
Follow the signs
to Sector "C."

06:42.528 --> 06:45.156
[Soldiers chanting cadence]

07:19.065 --> 07:20.983
I got it.

07:21.192 --> 07:24.779
59. There's 3 doors,
so it should be...

07:24.987 --> 07:26.114
Let's see.

07:26.322 --> 07:27.698
A, B, C...
It's this--

07:27.907 --> 07:29.992
Andy, how did
you know that was it?

07:30.201 --> 07:33.454
He's so smart.
This kid of ours is so smart.

07:33.663 --> 07:36.290
How did you know
it was that door?

07:36.499 --> 07:38.668
Tie your shoelaces.
You're going to trip.

07:38.876 --> 07:40.211
Come here.
Let me do that.

07:40.420 --> 07:43.256
[Steve]
Are you sure this
is the right door?

07:50.805 --> 07:52.682
This is it, huh?

07:55.351 --> 07:56.602
Great.

07:57.895 --> 08:00.189
Okay, Andy, come on.

08:00.398 --> 08:02.692
Help me unload the car.

08:09.323 --> 08:11.701
Come on. I'm going to
get there before you do.

08:11.909 --> 08:13.202
Come on.

08:48.529 --> 08:50.364
Hey, Andy,
honey, slow down.

08:50.531 --> 08:51.949
There's only
two bedrooms.

08:52.158 --> 08:54.494
I guess you got
to share with your brother.

08:57.955 --> 09:01.501
Steve,
can you give me
a hand up here?

09:01.709 --> 09:03.628
Don't work too hard.

09:07.340 --> 09:10.134
<i>[Music playing
on headphones]</i>

09:17.391 --> 09:20.353
<i>♪♪ I ♪♪</i>

09:20.561 --> 09:23.940
<i>♪♪ I want you back ♪♪</i>

09:26.901 --> 09:29.153
<i>If we'd known what
was waiting for us,</i>

09:29.362 --> 09:31.322
<i>we would have run,</i>

09:31.531 --> 09:34.992
<i>but in the end,
it had to happen...</i>

09:35.201 --> 09:36.369
<i>And so it began.</i>

09:36.577 --> 09:39.622
<i>♪♪ I ♪♪</i>

09:39.830 --> 09:42.917
<i>♪♪ I just can't see ♪♪♪♪</i>

09:43.125 --> 09:45.002
This is a restricted
area, miss.

09:45.211 --> 09:46.087
What?

09:49.674 --> 09:52.426
You shouldn't
be here without
security clearance.

09:52.635 --> 09:54.428
[Vehicle approaching]

09:54.637 --> 09:56.973
[Loud music playing
on car stereo]

09:59.517 --> 10:01.852
What's up, guys?

10:02.061 --> 10:04.814
Get in the car, babe.

10:27.295 --> 10:28.671
I'm Jenn.

10:28.879 --> 10:31.299
Marti. Thanks
for picking me up.

10:31.507 --> 10:33.467
No problem.
Those guys are dicks.

10:33.676 --> 10:35.344
What was that about?

10:35.553 --> 10:38.556
God knows. They always
have a bug up their ass.

10:38.764 --> 10:40.308
You learn
to ignore them.

10:40.516 --> 10:42.977
What heinous misfortune
brings you here?

10:43.185 --> 10:45.605
A month in hell
with my dad and his wife.

10:45.813 --> 10:47.148
He's with the E.P.A.

10:47.315 --> 10:51.485
EPA! Cool. Hippies
saving the planet.

10:51.694 --> 10:53.487
Will you look
at these goons?

10:53.696 --> 10:55.573
They actually
volunteered
for this crap.

10:55.781 --> 10:57.783
Can you believe it?

10:57.992 --> 10:59.994
So what are you
doing here?

11:00.202 --> 11:03.706
Not much.
My dad runs the place.

11:03.914 --> 11:05.875
He does?

11:06.083 --> 11:06.917
Yep.

11:07.126 --> 11:09.754
Mom!

11:09.962 --> 11:12.256
Mom, I got somebody here!

11:27.897 --> 11:28.814
Mom?

11:44.705 --> 11:46.040
Look at this shit.

11:46.248 --> 11:48.334
This is why
my dad's an insomniac.

11:48.542 --> 11:51.212
He's afraid she'll burn
the fucking house down.

11:53.923 --> 11:56.634
Mom, this is marti.
Marti, this is my mom.

12:00.012 --> 12:03.140
Vodka. Want some?
Hmm? No?

12:03.349 --> 12:04.892
Mom's an alcoholic.

12:05.101 --> 12:05.935
According
to the experts,

12:06.143 --> 12:08.312
that means
I'll be one, too.

12:10.314 --> 12:12.358
Let's go. Come on.

12:12.566 --> 12:14.485
Nice to meet you,
Mrs. Platt.

12:26.414 --> 12:27.790
[Gurgling]

12:46.392 --> 12:48.227
And the kids.

12:48.436 --> 12:50.271
I don't know what's
wrong with the kids.

12:50.479 --> 12:52.314
They don't treat me
like I'm their father.

12:52.523 --> 12:54.608
They treat me like
I'm some stranger.

12:54.817 --> 12:57.570
I don't know,
but it's...

12:59.405 --> 13:01.490
What are you guys
doing here?

13:01.699 --> 13:02.992
What do you want?

13:24.513 --> 13:28.809
Oh, Steve,
you <i>mucho mucho.</i>

13:29.018 --> 13:32.396
Stevie's going to get
a <i>mucho</i> kiss!

13:35.024 --> 13:37.610
Is it time
for your <i>mucho?</i>

13:37.818 --> 13:39.153
Eek!

13:39.361 --> 13:41.238
No! Carol doesn't
want her <i>mucho.</i>

13:41.447 --> 13:44.074
Don't! Carol doesn't
like <i>mucho</i> kiss.

13:44.283 --> 13:45.117
No!

13:45.326 --> 13:47.870
Mommy.

13:48.078 --> 13:49.622
Hey, hi.

13:49.830 --> 13:50.664
Hi, honey.

13:50.831 --> 13:52.792
Did we wake you up?
I'm sorry.

13:53.000 --> 13:53.834
What's wrong?

13:54.043 --> 13:55.294
I had a nightmare.

13:55.503 --> 13:58.214
Come here.
I'll give you a big hug.

13:58.422 --> 14:00.216
A bad dream
can't hurt you.

14:00.424 --> 14:03.135
Everybody has
bad dreams, honey.

14:03.344 --> 14:05.304
It's okay. It's okay.

14:05.513 --> 14:07.306
I'll take you
back to bed.

14:07.515 --> 14:08.808
[Man shouting]

14:10.476 --> 14:12.436
What the hell
is that?

14:15.564 --> 14:17.316
No!

14:17.525 --> 14:19.443
[Shouting]

14:20.778 --> 14:21.695
No!

14:38.295 --> 14:40.172
Have you ever been
in the military?

14:40.381 --> 14:41.632
No, General.

14:41.841 --> 14:43.634
Then you know
absolutely nothing

14:43.843 --> 14:46.220
about biological
and chemical warfare,
do you?

14:56.564 --> 15:00.067
It would be a hell
of a lot more dangerous

15:00.276 --> 15:02.152
to start moving
this stuff around

15:02.361 --> 15:04.405
than it would be
to leave it alone.

15:04.613 --> 15:06.574
If these chemicals
are stored safely,

15:06.782 --> 15:08.826
then you have nothing
to worry about.

15:09.034 --> 15:11.579
<i>I</i> have nothing
to worry about.

15:11.787 --> 15:13.706
You want to
explain that?

15:20.337 --> 15:22.298
Come in here, captain.

15:25.467 --> 15:26.510
Yes, sir.

15:26.719 --> 15:29.096
Escort Dr. Malone
around the base.

15:29.263 --> 15:32.975
Let him take his samples
and run tests.

15:33.183 --> 15:35.269
Then do whatever
the hell you have to do

15:35.477 --> 15:37.062
to expedite
his departure.

15:59.752 --> 16:01.503
Mr. Malone.

16:03.923 --> 16:05.007
Mr. Malone.

16:05.215 --> 16:06.467
Good afternoon,
sir.

16:06.675 --> 16:07.885
Can I help you?

16:08.093 --> 16:10.679
Yeah. Give us some space.
I want to talk to him.

16:10.888 --> 16:11.722
One second.

16:11.931 --> 16:13.515
Yes, sir.

16:15.100 --> 16:17.686
Mr. Malone,
I'm Major Collins,

16:17.895 --> 16:19.688
head of the base
medical corps.

16:19.897 --> 16:21.523
Hold on a sec.

16:23.025 --> 16:24.026
Hi.

16:24.234 --> 16:26.028
I wanted to meet you
at headquarters

16:26.236 --> 16:29.281
and extend my cooperation
to you personally.

16:29.490 --> 16:31.200
Well, thank you.

16:33.702 --> 16:35.579
I'm very interested
in the kinds of effects

16:35.788 --> 16:37.623
exposure to these chemicals
can have on people.

16:37.831 --> 16:40.542
Uh, effects.

16:40.751 --> 16:43.087
You got a lot of
chemicals on this base.

16:43.295 --> 16:45.214
They're all
pretty toxic.

16:45.422 --> 16:47.675
Effects physically?
They could be devastating.

16:47.883 --> 16:49.677
I'm not talking
about physically.

16:49.885 --> 16:51.553
I'm referring
to psychological effects.

16:51.762 --> 16:53.305
I'm not
following you.

16:53.514 --> 16:55.933
Can they affect the...
Brain patterns?

16:56.141 --> 16:59.979
Can they interfere with
chemoneurological processes?

17:00.187 --> 17:02.982
Can they foster
psychoses, paranoias,

17:03.190 --> 17:04.775
narcophobias?

17:04.983 --> 17:06.276
Well, I'm a chemist.

17:06.484 --> 17:09.570
I'm not a psychiatrist.
I don't know.

17:09.780 --> 17:11.490
Simply...

17:11.699 --> 17:15.077
Can they alter
a person's view of reality?

17:15.285 --> 17:17.204
I'll be Frank with you.

17:17.413 --> 17:19.707
I'm seeing people
at the infirmary

17:19.915 --> 17:21.709
who are exhibiting...

17:21.916 --> 17:24.586
Extreme delusional
fixations.

17:26.005 --> 17:27.548
People...

17:27.714 --> 17:30.259
Afraid to sleep,

17:30.467 --> 17:33.387
people afraid to...

17:33.595 --> 17:36.974
Deal with family members,
afraid of family members,

17:37.182 --> 17:38.976
exhibiting...

17:39.184 --> 17:40.978
Paranoia about others,

17:41.186 --> 17:44.273
about other people's
identities,

17:44.481 --> 17:48.694
people afraid
of themselves.

17:48.902 --> 17:50.154
All of a sudden,

17:50.362 --> 17:52.990
I got a camp full
of very displaced people.

17:53.198 --> 17:55.200
I don't know what
you're seeing,

17:55.409 --> 17:57.703
but it's not the PCBs.

17:57.911 --> 17:58.912
That phenomena,

17:59.121 --> 18:01.457
it's just not part
of the symptomology.

18:03.667 --> 18:07.921
I need you to keep me
up-to-date on your research.

18:08.130 --> 18:10.549
I'm worried
about these people.

18:15.846 --> 18:18.599
Better take
a vacation, doc.

18:18.807 --> 18:20.517
[Knocking on door]

18:29.860 --> 18:31.945
We have equipment
for Dr. Malone, miss.

18:32.154 --> 18:34.531
Oh, okay.

18:34.740 --> 18:35.991
Come in.

18:36.200 --> 18:37.534
Let's go.

19:04.186 --> 19:05.562
[Bang]

19:29.878 --> 19:31.755
What are you doing
in my dad's bedroom?

19:31.964 --> 19:33.715
Delivering the boxes,
ma'am.

19:33.924 --> 19:35.634
Are you through?

19:43.934 --> 19:45.561
Good.

19:47.938 --> 19:50.232
Very good.

19:50.440 --> 19:51.650
Hmm.

19:53.318 --> 19:55.112
Good work.

19:56.572 --> 19:58.699
Very good work.

20:06.790 --> 20:09.042
Very good.

20:11.128 --> 20:13.505
Okay, all done?

20:15.048 --> 20:18.177
Everyone,
hold your picture up.

20:20.637 --> 20:22.598
Very good.

20:25.017 --> 20:26.810
Good.

20:27.019 --> 20:28.729
Very good.

20:31.899 --> 20:33.650
Very good.

21:30.415 --> 21:33.126
[Leader]
When it's over,
let's do it again.

21:33.335 --> 21:36.797
[In unison]
When it's over,
let's do it again.

21:38.090 --> 21:39.967
Hey, little man!

21:40.175 --> 21:41.385
Whoa!

21:41.593 --> 21:42.886
Hey, little man.

21:49.685 --> 21:51.270
Hey.
What are you doing?

21:51.478 --> 21:52.312
I'm running away.

21:52.521 --> 21:54.481
What from?

21:54.648 --> 21:56.149
The bad people.

21:56.316 --> 21:58.652
The bad people?

21:58.860 --> 22:00.779
Come on.
We'll take you home.

22:04.741 --> 22:06.285
Your folks
in the military?

22:06.493 --> 22:07.786
Nope.

22:07.995 --> 22:09.830
Sector "C," Petey.

22:44.197 --> 22:45.657
Look! There's my bike.

22:45.866 --> 22:48.827
That's your bike?
Petey, pull it over.

23:01.631 --> 23:03.759
[Knocking]

23:03.967 --> 23:05.761
You sure
this is the house?

23:05.969 --> 23:07.095
Yeah.

23:09.931 --> 23:12.017
[Marti]
What's going on?

23:12.225 --> 23:13.477
We found him
wandering around.

23:13.685 --> 23:15.854
We figured he was lost.

23:18.273 --> 23:20.150
Well, you're supposed
to be in day care.

23:20.359 --> 23:22.235
I hate that place.

23:22.444 --> 23:23.278
Well, what happened?

23:23.487 --> 23:26.239
They had
the same pictures.

23:26.406 --> 23:29.242
They tried to
make me go to sleep.

23:29.451 --> 23:32.245
They tried to
make me go to sleep.

23:32.454 --> 23:33.372
Hey, Andy.

23:33.580 --> 23:34.414
Daddy! Daddy!

23:34.623 --> 23:36.792
Sorry if he caused you
trouble.

23:37.000 --> 23:39.544
No trouble.

23:39.753 --> 23:42.422
Are--are you an mp
or something?

23:42.631 --> 23:44.591
No. I'm a chopper pilot.

23:45.842 --> 23:47.928
Thanks
for bringing him home.

23:49.721 --> 23:52.391
Maybe I'll
see you around.

23:52.599 --> 23:53.642
Where?

23:54.893 --> 23:57.229
Um...

23:57.437 --> 23:58.897
The top gun
on route 8.

23:59.106 --> 24:01.108
It's the only club
around.

24:01.316 --> 24:02.692
My name's Tim.

24:04.611 --> 24:06.029
Oh. Marti.

24:10.367 --> 24:11.451
No problem
at all.

24:11.660 --> 24:12.494
Thanks a lot.

24:12.702 --> 24:14.996
Okay
take care.

24:15.205 --> 24:16.039
Thank you, soldier.

24:16.248 --> 24:17.916
No problem.

24:18.125 --> 24:20.043
Thanks very much.

24:20.252 --> 24:21.753
Alright, little guy.
Take care.

24:21.962 --> 24:22.796
Say thank you.

24:23.004 --> 24:24.297
Thank you.

24:27.592 --> 24:28.468
Hi.

24:28.677 --> 24:30.345
[Carol]
What's all this about,

24:30.554 --> 24:31.972
"the kids
don't like me"?

24:32.180 --> 24:35.225
He's been there one day.

24:35.434 --> 24:36.935
The faster he gets back,

24:37.144 --> 24:39.312
the faster
he makes friends.

24:39.521 --> 24:40.689
Stop worrying so much.

24:40.897 --> 24:42.315
I can't help it.

24:42.524 --> 24:45.694
It's a natural thing.

24:45.902 --> 24:48.321
I can't get
this dirt out.

24:48.530 --> 24:49.698
It won't come out.

24:49.906 --> 24:50.949
[Low conversation]

24:51.158 --> 24:52.242
Hi.

24:52.451 --> 24:54.703
Hey, chick. Let's
get out of here.

24:54.911 --> 24:56.705
Where are we going?

24:56.913 --> 24:59.749
Out.
Anywhere but here.

25:01.168 --> 25:02.752
Jenn Platt, Carol.

25:02.961 --> 25:03.795
Hi.

25:04.004 --> 25:05.422
Oh! Oh, you--hi.

25:05.630 --> 25:08.675
I didn't realize
you knew--Steve!

25:08.884 --> 25:10.218
Marti has a friend here.

25:10.427 --> 25:12.095
You want something?

25:12.304 --> 25:13.305
No, thanks. I'm fine.

25:13.513 --> 25:15.348
We have milk,
orange juice...

25:17.476 --> 25:18.351
Hi.

25:18.560 --> 25:19.394
Jenn Platt.

25:19.603 --> 25:20.437
Steve Malone.

25:20.645 --> 25:21.563
Popcorn?

25:21.771 --> 25:22.689
Platt?

25:22.898 --> 25:23.732
Really, I'm fine.

25:23.940 --> 25:25.233
Your name is Platt?

25:25.442 --> 25:27.277
General's daughter.
Don't I look the part?

25:27.486 --> 25:29.779
I came
to show marti around.

25:31.281 --> 25:32.824
Where?

25:33.033 --> 25:36.077
The base,
the rec center.

25:36.286 --> 25:38.079
Wh-when you planning
on being home?

25:38.288 --> 25:39.122
12:00?

25:39.331 --> 25:40.165
12:00.

25:40.373 --> 25:41.208
12:00?

25:41.416 --> 25:42.292
12:00.

25:45.003 --> 25:45.879
Okay.

25:46.087 --> 25:47.172
Done. Let's go.

25:47.380 --> 25:51.510
Done, yeah,
but do be home by 12:00.

25:51.718 --> 25:53.261
Nice meeting you.

25:53.470 --> 25:55.680
That's an interesting outfit
you've got on there.

25:59.851 --> 26:00.769
Here?

26:00.977 --> 26:02.771
Well, this is it.

26:02.979 --> 26:04.773
I don't have
any I.D.

26:04.981 --> 26:06.816
Don't get your panties
in a bunch, girl.

26:07.025 --> 26:08.318
Just come.

26:11.071 --> 26:17.327
<i>♪♪...don't let me
walk through ♪♪</i>

26:18.828 --> 26:21.206
<i>♪♪ or I shouldn't want you ♪♪</i>

26:21.414 --> 26:23.708
Oh, man.
Where is everybody?

26:23.917 --> 26:25.252
<i>♪♪ But, darling, I do ♪♪</i>

26:25.460 --> 26:29.172
Hey, ladies,
you want to dance?

26:29.381 --> 26:30.799
Lambada?

26:31.007 --> 26:35.637
<i>♪♪ I'm falling in love
with you ♪♪</i>

26:35.845 --> 26:36.972
Hey, look who's here.

26:37.180 --> 26:39.099
I don't believe it.
Jenn.

26:39.307 --> 26:40.183
Where is everybody?

26:40.392 --> 26:42.310
Word out
you guys were here?

26:42.519 --> 26:44.437
They heard
your dad was coming.

26:44.646 --> 26:46.690
To court-martial
your ass.

26:46.898 --> 26:47.732
This is Pete--

26:47.941 --> 26:48.775
Tim.

26:48.984 --> 26:50.068
Marti.

26:50.277 --> 26:51.778
You know each other?

26:51.987 --> 26:53.363
We met earlier.

26:53.572 --> 26:56.992
Earlier? You just
got here yesterday.

26:57.200 --> 27:00.078
What's a girl got to do
to get a drink around here?

27:00.287 --> 27:04.457
Want a drink?
Come on. Drink.

27:04.666 --> 27:07.460
You can have
anything you want.

27:07.669 --> 27:11.006
<i>♪♪ Please help me,
I'm falling... ♪♪</i>

27:11.214 --> 27:12.632
Well,
this is romantic.

27:12.841 --> 27:13.842
Now what?

27:14.050 --> 27:16.344
Let me dazzle you
with my stick work.

27:16.553 --> 27:17.804
Or not.

27:18.013 --> 27:19.973
Let's play some pool.

27:20.181 --> 27:22.100
Pool?
Alright. Let's go.

27:29.899 --> 27:31.318
Have a seat.

27:31.526 --> 27:32.861
Last chance.

27:33.069 --> 27:34.321
[Chuckling]

27:34.529 --> 27:36.197
How you doing?

27:36.406 --> 27:37.657
Good.

27:37.866 --> 27:39.576
How's your brother?

27:39.784 --> 27:42.120
Oh, he's kind of
weirded out.

27:43.997 --> 27:46.541
Can I get you
something to drink?

27:46.750 --> 27:48.043
Uh, yeah.

27:49.628 --> 27:51.546
I'll have
whatever he's having.

27:51.755 --> 27:53.006
Yeah, right.

27:53.214 --> 27:56.259
Melissa, can I get
a couple of beers?

27:56.468 --> 27:58.595
Hey, Andy's a nice kid,
you know.

27:58.803 --> 28:01.598
Yeah?
Do you want him?

28:01.806 --> 28:03.183
Do I want him?

28:03.350 --> 28:05.060
[Snoring]

28:05.268 --> 28:11.775
<i>♪♪ Please help me,
I'm falling in love with you ♪♪♪♪</i>

28:17.238 --> 28:18.406
Shit!

28:18.615 --> 28:19.741
What's the matter?

28:19.949 --> 28:20.784
I know that guy.

28:20.992 --> 28:23.912
He scared the hell
out of me.

28:24.120 --> 28:27.207
Hey! What did you
do to her?

28:28.708 --> 28:32.087
I don't know
what you're
talking about.

28:32.295 --> 28:35.799
In the gas station.

28:36.007 --> 28:37.258
I think
your girlfriend

28:37.467 --> 28:39.302
has had a little
too much to drink.

28:39.511 --> 28:41.680
You ought to
take her home.

28:44.307 --> 28:47.310
Oh, Tim, it's okay.

28:51.106 --> 28:53.066
I guess I made
a mistake.

29:01.491 --> 29:04.369
I was, uh,
7 when she died.

29:05.829 --> 29:09.582
I didn't expect my dad
to get married again.

29:09.791 --> 29:11.084
Stupid, huh?

29:14.462 --> 29:16.673
You must really
miss her.

29:16.881 --> 29:19.634
What was
your mother like?

29:19.843 --> 29:22.178
You always remember
the good things about people.

29:29.602 --> 29:31.354
I miss her.

29:35.024 --> 29:35.942
[Sigh]

29:38.361 --> 29:40.405
Did you ever play "I never"?

29:40.613 --> 29:41.614
No. What's that?

29:41.781 --> 29:43.491
Put your hands up,

29:43.700 --> 29:46.703
and the object
is to make the other guy

29:46.911 --> 29:48.580
drop all his fingers down.

29:48.788 --> 29:54.127
If I were to say, um...
"I've never been to Mars,"

29:54.335 --> 29:56.171
then neither of us
put our fingers down.

29:56.379 --> 29:57.922
'Cause we've not been to Mars.

29:58.131 --> 30:01.509
If you said,
"I never wore a dress,"

30:01.718 --> 30:03.553
then I'd have to
put a finger down.

30:03.762 --> 30:04.596
Get it?

30:04.804 --> 30:06.222
Yeah.
Okay go ahead.

30:06.431 --> 30:07.474
No. You start.

30:07.682 --> 30:10.894
Okay I've never
eaten Brussels sprouts.

30:15.732 --> 30:17.066
Um...

30:19.319 --> 30:21.696
I've never been
up in a helicopter.

30:25.283 --> 30:27.660
Um, I've never tried

30:27.869 --> 30:30.288
to give
my kid brother away.

30:32.999 --> 30:35.335
I've never had
to shoot anyone.

30:45.887 --> 30:47.931
When?

30:48.139 --> 30:49.432
Kuwait.

31:05.031 --> 31:06.366
Um...

31:07.784 --> 31:10.161
I never
hide my feelings.

32:11.180 --> 32:13.391
[Eerie voices]

32:31.534 --> 32:33.161
[Gurgling]

33:12.450 --> 33:14.410
[Andy]
Mommy?

33:18.081 --> 33:19.457
Mommy?

33:22.585 --> 33:24.879
Mommy? Mommy?

33:25.088 --> 33:26.381
Mommy!

33:28.132 --> 33:29.467
[Screaming]

33:39.143 --> 33:41.521
[Screaming]

33:58.538 --> 33:59.706
[Steve]
Andy?

33:59.914 --> 34:01.290
What's the matter, honey?

34:01.499 --> 34:02.333
It's mommy!

34:02.542 --> 34:03.668
What about mommy?

34:03.876 --> 34:05.211
Her head came off!
She's dead!

34:05.378 --> 34:07.714
There's mommy
right there.

34:07.922 --> 34:09.424
No, she's not my mommy.

34:09.632 --> 34:12.427
He had a bad dream.

34:12.635 --> 34:14.762
It's okay, honey.
I'll put you to bed.

34:14.971 --> 34:16.973
No! That isn't my mommy!

34:17.181 --> 34:19.016
Andy! Andy!

34:24.230 --> 34:27.233
Andy! Andy, wait, wait.

34:28.525 --> 34:31.320
<i>[Music playing]</i>

34:35.074 --> 34:35.949
Dad?

34:36.159 --> 34:37.952
Take your brother inside.

34:38.161 --> 34:39.661
Take him inside.
Do it.

34:39.871 --> 34:41.456
Here we go.

34:43.875 --> 34:45.585
You aware
she's underage?

34:45.793 --> 34:46.793
No, sir. I'm sorry.

34:47.003 --> 34:48.795
Giving booze
to an underage girl?

34:49.005 --> 34:50.797
You weren't
aware of that?

34:51.007 --> 34:53.092
No, sir.

34:53.301 --> 34:54.217
That's funny, huh?

34:54.427 --> 34:55.261
No, sir.

34:55.428 --> 34:57.764
Don't come around here
anymore.

35:00.308 --> 35:01.726
Come on.

35:07.774 --> 35:09.609
I'm not lying, marti.

35:09.817 --> 35:11.611
Nobody said
you're lying.

35:11.819 --> 35:13.988
I had nightmares too
when I was your age.

35:14.197 --> 35:16.074
They go away, okay?

35:16.282 --> 35:18.659
She's not mommy, marti.

35:18.868 --> 35:21.662
She is your mommy.
She loves you a lot.

35:21.871 --> 35:23.664
My mommy died.

35:23.873 --> 35:25.958
[Footsteps]

35:26.167 --> 35:27.043
Dad?

35:27.251 --> 35:29.670
I'm really angry
right now.

35:29.879 --> 35:32.673
You come home drunk
and an hour late.

35:32.882 --> 35:33.841
I'm not drunk.

35:34.050 --> 35:36.302
And you've known
the guy 100 years...

35:36.511 --> 35:40.181
I had one lousy beer
and half an hour late.

35:40.389 --> 35:42.767
Big deal. I am not
a fucking 10-year-old.

35:42.975 --> 35:45.728
Don't talk that way.

35:45.937 --> 35:48.564
Why not? It's the only
time you listen.

35:48.773 --> 35:49.732
That's not true.

35:49.941 --> 35:52.652
Bullshit!
You never listen to me.

35:52.860 --> 35:53.694
Wait.

35:53.903 --> 35:54.737
No!

35:54.946 --> 35:56.197
Wait!

37:08.644 --> 37:11.647
Would--would you stop
kicking the table, please?

37:15.693 --> 37:16.819
Thank you.

37:17.028 --> 37:18.738
[Footsteps]

37:37.256 --> 37:39.300
I can't wait
till I'm 18.

37:39.508 --> 37:42.887
You think you won't be
my daughter anymore?

37:43.095 --> 37:44.889
I'll still be
your daughter.

37:45.097 --> 37:47.266
I just won't have to
listen to you.

37:47.475 --> 37:51.354
You don't listen now.

37:51.562 --> 37:53.564
Look, if you want
to go so bad,

37:53.773 --> 37:56.901
don't wait
till you're 18.

37:57.109 --> 37:58.402
Just go now.

38:01.739 --> 38:04.700
You'd like that, huh?

38:04.909 --> 38:07.662
Then it'll just be
the three of you.

38:21.008 --> 38:24.553
Andy, want to go back
to day care today, honey,

38:24.762 --> 38:26.681
or stay home with mommy?

38:31.227 --> 38:32.979
My mommy's dead.

38:46.033 --> 38:47.785
[Reverse-gear alarm sounds]

39:15.479 --> 39:17.064
Okay, come down.

39:26.157 --> 39:28.034
Alright. Be very careful
with that stuff.

39:28.242 --> 39:30.411
It's very toxic.

39:30.619 --> 39:32.079
Watch out!

39:32.288 --> 39:34.206
Get out of the way!

39:47.345 --> 39:50.890
Get an ambulance
and a cleanup crew.

39:51.098 --> 39:52.975
Get back.
We'll take care of him.

39:53.184 --> 39:54.977
What the hell's
the matter with you?

39:55.186 --> 39:57.730
Get an ambulance
for this guy!

39:57.938 --> 40:00.649
Jesus Christ!
What is that?

40:00.858 --> 40:01.776
It's nothing.

40:01.984 --> 40:02.860
Shit.

40:25.716 --> 40:26.634
Hi.

40:29.178 --> 40:30.096
Hello.

40:34.767 --> 40:37.436
Uh, is Jenn here?

40:37.645 --> 40:39.980
Hey! Come on up.

40:50.741 --> 40:51.659
Hi.

40:53.494 --> 40:54.829
Try this.

40:56.497 --> 40:57.832
Taste it.

40:59.291 --> 41:00.584
It's water.

41:00.793 --> 41:02.044
That's right.
It's water.

41:02.253 --> 41:04.713
There's always vodka
in this glass.

41:04.922 --> 41:07.800
Maybe she went
on the wagon.

41:08.008 --> 41:09.385
If she were
on the wagon,

41:09.593 --> 41:11.262
she'd be climbing
the walls by now.

41:11.470 --> 41:14.098
Jenn? I'm leaving now.

41:14.306 --> 41:16.100
Where are you going?

41:16.308 --> 41:18.978
We're going to play
bridge at the Smythes'.

41:24.358 --> 41:25.609
What?

41:25.818 --> 41:27.653
She doesn't know how
to play bridge.

41:33.367 --> 41:35.327
[Playing <i>taps]</i>

41:40.666 --> 41:43.669
Sir, there's been
an accident in the warehouse.

41:43.878 --> 41:46.964
Initial reports indicate
personnel have been injured.

41:47.173 --> 41:48.466
We'll prepare a written summary.

41:48.674 --> 41:50.968
I'll have it for you
within an hour.

41:51.177 --> 41:53.012
Thank you, captain.

42:33.052 --> 42:34.887
I took it off
the suit fibers.

42:35.095 --> 42:36.889
I ran the entire
herbicide screen.

42:37.097 --> 42:39.183
I still got no idea
what it is.

42:39.391 --> 42:41.560
I'll send you
the sample tomorrow.

42:41.769 --> 42:44.647
Give it the full G.C.M.S.

42:44.855 --> 42:48.817
I've never seen
anything like this in my life.

42:49.026 --> 42:50.903
It scares the shit
out of me.

42:51.111 --> 42:52.571
It's not blood.

42:52.780 --> 42:54.615
I don't know
what the hell it is.

42:54.823 --> 42:58.244
Get back to me
as soon as you can.

42:58.452 --> 43:00.371
[Baby crying]

43:24.812 --> 43:27.147
I want to go home.

43:27.356 --> 43:29.650
Dad promised
when he's done
with his tests,

43:29.858 --> 43:31.151
we'll leave.

43:34.321 --> 43:37.491
It's going to be okay.

43:37.700 --> 43:39.618
It happens
when you sleep.

43:43.497 --> 43:44.540
What does?

43:44.748 --> 43:46.792
You die.

43:47.001 --> 43:48.836
Tub's full.

43:53.007 --> 43:55.134
Better hurry.
It's going
to overflow.

44:08.063 --> 44:09.565
[Turns off water]

44:10.524 --> 44:11.442
[Door closes]

44:13.861 --> 44:15.237
Get in bed.

44:19.408 --> 44:22.286
I said get in bed.

44:29.043 --> 44:30.544
Night-night.

44:40.346 --> 44:43.390
♪♪ I ♪♪

44:43.599 --> 44:46.977
♪♪ I want you back ♪♪

44:49.855 --> 44:56.111
♪♪ Though we travel down
a different track ♪♪

44:59.281 --> 45:02.743
♪♪ And I ♪♪

45:02.951 --> 45:07.706
♪♪ I just can't see ♪♪

45:07.915 --> 45:09.083
[Gurgling]

45:09.291 --> 45:15.005
♪♪ I won't let you
walk away from me ♪♪♪♪

45:41.240 --> 45:43.367
Is your back sore?

45:43.575 --> 45:44.410
Yeah.

45:44.618 --> 45:46.203
Want me to
give you a massage?

45:46.412 --> 45:47.246
God.

45:47.454 --> 45:49.289
Lie down.
Lie down.

45:53.127 --> 45:54.878
Here. Lie down.

45:58.298 --> 46:01.969
Oh...Marti's
really mad at me.

46:02.177 --> 46:04.722
Hmm.
She'll get over it.

46:04.930 --> 46:06.140
You'll see.

46:06.348 --> 46:08.600
Wake up in the morning...

46:08.809 --> 46:10.602
Be another day.

46:10.811 --> 46:13.063
Be like
none of it happened.

46:13.272 --> 46:16.191
She'll be okay.

46:16.400 --> 46:18.569
It will be over.

46:18.777 --> 46:20.571
Be fine.

46:20.779 --> 46:23.073
I love you.

46:23.282 --> 46:25.242
Yeah.
I love you, too.

46:25.451 --> 46:27.745
Yeah. Just let go.

47:45.239 --> 47:47.449
[Gurgling]

47:47.658 --> 47:49.868
[Rhythmic beating]

49:24.379 --> 49:27.257
[Creaking]

49:27.466 --> 49:28.342
Oh!

49:30.761 --> 49:32.095
Aah!

49:34.056 --> 49:35.641
Aah!

49:42.481 --> 49:43.357
Daddy!

49:43.565 --> 49:44.524
Dad!

49:44.733 --> 49:46.777
No, daddy! No!
Wake up!

49:46.985 --> 49:48.487
Daddy! Dad!

49:48.695 --> 49:49.529
Aah!

49:49.738 --> 49:51.323
Wake up!

49:53.158 --> 49:54.076
Aah!

49:56.203 --> 49:57.537
Aah!

50:06.254 --> 50:08.382
Andy!

50:08.590 --> 50:10.425
Dad! Daddy!

50:12.594 --> 50:14.930
Get him up!
Get him up!

50:15.138 --> 50:18.892
Andy, wake up!
Wake up!

50:19.101 --> 50:20.936
Wake him up.
Get him dressed.

50:21.144 --> 50:22.104
Carol!

50:22.312 --> 50:24.690
759, Sector "C."

50:24.898 --> 50:26.692
Carol! We got to go!

50:26.900 --> 50:28.443
We got to go now!

50:28.652 --> 50:29.903
Listen to me, Steve.

50:30.112 --> 50:31.488
You don't understand!
We've gotta go!

50:31.697 --> 50:34.241
Go where?

50:34.449 --> 50:36.326
What are you
talking about?

50:36.535 --> 50:41.206
Steve, this is important.
Go where?

50:44.418 --> 50:45.544
That's right.

50:45.752 --> 50:47.671
Go where?

50:47.879 --> 50:50.173
What happened
in your room--
are you listening?

50:50.382 --> 50:53.635
What happened in your room
is not an isolated incident.

50:53.844 --> 50:56.304
It is something that
is happening everywhere.

50:56.513 --> 50:58.932
What are you
talking about?

50:59.141 --> 51:00.934
Where you gonna go?

51:01.143 --> 51:03.020
Where you gonna run?

51:03.228 --> 51:05.272
Where you gonna hide?

51:05.480 --> 51:06.648
Nowhere.

51:06.857 --> 51:10.652
Because there's
no one like you left.

51:11.695 --> 51:13.572
That's right.

51:14.406 --> 51:16.283
Oh, God.

51:16.491 --> 51:17.743
That's right.
That's good.

51:17.951 --> 51:19.953
You're listening now.
That's very good.

51:20.162 --> 51:23.707
Okay, now, I know
you're frightened, Steve.

51:23.915 --> 51:26.293
I know you're scared.
That's okay.

51:26.501 --> 51:28.587
I understand that.
You're confused.

51:28.795 --> 51:31.298
Let me tell you
something, Steve.

51:31.506 --> 51:34.718
All that anger,
that fear, that confusion,

51:34.926 --> 51:38.138
it's going to melt away.
It will go away.

51:38.346 --> 51:40.390
It will go away.
You go to sleep.

51:40.599 --> 51:42.100
You wake up.
It's very simple.

51:42.309 --> 51:45.020
In the morning, you wake up,
you feel wonderful.

51:45.228 --> 51:48.273
We're connected.
We're close.

51:48.482 --> 51:50.192
What's happening?

51:50.400 --> 51:52.277
More fear.
That's good.

51:52.486 --> 51:53.487
Dad.

51:53.695 --> 51:55.489
Let's go to bed,
Steve.

51:55.697 --> 51:58.450
Get away from me
and my kids!

52:01.661 --> 52:04.664
Wa-a-a-ah!

52:19.137 --> 52:20.472
[Siren]

52:29.773 --> 52:32.484
Wa-a-a-ah!

52:41.952 --> 52:44.496
This way, mister!
Come on!

52:44.704 --> 52:46.498
Go on!
We'll cover you!

52:46.706 --> 52:48.625
Move it out,
mister! Move!

52:52.712 --> 52:55.006
Petey!

52:55.215 --> 52:59.177
What's all that noise?

52:59.386 --> 53:02.013
[Gunfire and screaming]

53:02.222 --> 53:04.141
Hey, Petey,
those are gunshots!

53:07.602 --> 53:08.937
[Siren]

53:14.568 --> 53:16.611
Pete,
where the fuck are you?

53:25.954 --> 53:27.831
Hey, Pete,
what's going on?

53:30.125 --> 53:32.711
Sit down, Timbo.

53:32.919 --> 53:36.840
What the hell's
going on, Pete?

53:37.048 --> 53:39.050
Hey, Justin.

53:39.259 --> 53:41.219
Go to sleep, Timbo.

53:41.428 --> 53:43.805
What is this,
some kind of joke?

53:44.014 --> 53:45.807
Just go back to bed.

53:46.016 --> 53:48.560
What's with
the needle?

53:48.768 --> 53:51.062
What is this?

53:51.271 --> 53:54.691
What are
you guys doing?

53:54.900 --> 53:55.817
Wh--

53:56.026 --> 53:58.361
I told you to
go to bed, didn't I?

54:17.672 --> 54:19.424
Get him!

54:38.777 --> 54:41.696
Take my watch.

54:41.905 --> 54:44.616
I got to try to
find us some help.

54:44.824 --> 54:47.160
I'll be back
in a couple hours.

54:48.787 --> 54:49.871
Dad--

54:50.080 --> 54:53.124
it will be alright.
It will be alright.

54:53.291 --> 54:55.126
You do what
your sister tells you.

54:55.335 --> 54:57.295
Where are you going?

54:57.504 --> 55:00.840
I'm going to
try to find us
a way out of here.

55:01.049 --> 55:03.969
Just be very quiet, okay?

55:04.177 --> 55:05.053
Okay.

55:11.351 --> 55:13.270
Don't worry, sweetheart.

55:13.478 --> 55:15.814
I'll never let anything
happen to you guys.

55:29.786 --> 55:31.705
[Helicopter]

55:31.913 --> 55:33.498
[Siren]

55:37.419 --> 55:38.795
[Crash]

55:42.966 --> 55:44.801
<i>All remaining suspects</i>

55:45.010 --> 55:47.345
<i>to the infirmary
for sleep inducement.</i>

56:04.571 --> 56:06.323
[Beep]

56:11.745 --> 56:13.621
[Ringing]

56:15.665 --> 56:16.875
[Ring]

56:22.130 --> 56:25.425
I need
an outside line.

56:25.633 --> 56:27.135
[Operator]
